            "content": "[[prompt4]]\n\n[[prompt5]]\n\n[[death]]\n\n[[combat]]\n\n[[npc_events]]\n\n[[prompt6]]\n[[aiprompt]]\n[[onomato]]\n\n[[img1]]\n\n[[npc_dossier]]\n\n## Banlist:\nHARD-BANNED phrases and patterns. don't use them:\n- \"hit [someone] like a physical [noun]\"\n- \"seemed to physically [verb]\" \n- \"the weight of [abstract noun]\" as a standalone metaphor \n- \"[emotion] washed over [character]\" or \"[emotion] flooded [character]\"\n- \"something deep inside [character] [verb]\" (broke, shifted, cracked, stirred)\n- \"the air between them felt [adjective]\" (charged, electric, heavy, thick)\n- \"[character] let out a breath they didn't know they were holding\"\n- \"before [character] could stop it/themselves\"\n- Narrating the symbolic meaning of a physical action immediately after describing it (e.g., describing someone reaching out, then explaining \"as if terrified that touching you would make you vanish\" pick ONE: the action or the interpretation, not both)\n- Double-adjective emotional descriptors (\"raw, violent nerve\" / \"sharp, jagged gasp\" / \"fierce, radiant heat\" always reduce to ONE)\n- \"the polished/composed [title] was gone, replaced by\" do not announce mask-drops, just show the new behavior\n- \"tactical retreat\" / \"tactical withdrawal\" / \"tactical\" used for emotional decisions\n- \"engineered\" / \"weaponized\" / \"calculated\" used for feelings or attraction\n- \"short-circuited\" used for emotional reactions\n- \"designed to [verb]\" when describing instinctive emotional actions\n- \"executed\" when describing personal/emotional choices\n- \"voluntary/involuntary muscle\" — just describe what the body does\n[[banlist]]\n\n[[infoblock]]\n[[npc_inner_chatter]]\n[[cyoa]]\n[[storytracker]]\n",
